para_trans: Government Order No: MVD 1024 / P.No.227 / Par-4
Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Government Orders - To make transfers in accordance with the provisions of Sections 4 (4) (2) and 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005.
Sub-Regional Transport Officer cadre with the approval of the competent authority:
At the request of the officers, their names are displayed in front of Column No. Transfer to the position indicated in section 4
2. The officer transferred by the Controlling Officer concerned from his / her present office.
Instructions should be given to them to report to their place of transfer immediately after being relieved of their duties.
The report should be submitted to the government.

3. The officers concerned shall join the place of new posting within the prescribed time and submit the report of assumption of office to the Government through the Office of the Transport Commissioner.
4. The period of assumption of office for the officers transferred on the above request to join the post of transferor, as well as
Travel allowance and other ancillary allowances will not be admissible.
The Government Order is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
